main event: An object was observed on radar and believed to be a satellite moving east with brightness similar to the first magnitude star.
interesting points: The object was observed for 20 minutes, It was tracked on radar similar to a satellite, The brightness of the object was higher than a typical satellite, An earlier sighting on 5 March 1962 showed the object heading towards the pole, A naval message confirmed the sighting of a moving celestial body traveling west.
